## Pre-Commit Hooks

### Running Pre-Commit Checks

**IMPORTANT: Always activate the virtual environment before running pre-commit checks.**

The project uses pre-commit hooks to ensure code quality. These hooks run Black, isort, flake8, and pylint, which must be executed from the virtual environment.

```bash
# Activate virtual environment (required)
source venv/bin/activate

# Install pre-commit hooks (first time setup)
pre-commit install

# Run pre-commit checks on all files
pre-commit run --all-files

# Run pre-commit checks on staged files only (default)
pre-commit run

# Run a specific hook
pre-commit run black --all-files
pre-commit run flake8 --all-files
pre-commit run pylint --all-files
pre-commit run isort --all-files
```

### Manual Code Quality Checks

You can also run the code quality tools manually:

```bash
# Activate virtual environment (required)
source venv/bin/activate

# Format code with Black
black custom_components/ tests/

# Sort imports with isort
isort custom_components/ tests/

# Check code style with flake8
flake8 custom_components/ tests/

# Lint code with pylint
pylint custom_components/ tests/
```

### Virtual Environment Setup

All code quality checks must be run within the project's virtual environment:

```bash
# Activate virtual environment (required before running checks)
source venv/bin/activate

# Verify tools are available
black --version
isort --version
flake8 --version
pylint --version

# Deactivate when done (optional)
deactivate
```

**Note**: If the virtual environment is not activated, pre-commit hooks may fail or use incorrect tool versions.

